chnology-economist-daron-acemoglu-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20How%20much%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20know%2C%20does%20AI%20help%20white-collar%20professionals%20do%20their%20jobs%3F%20The%20productivity%20gains%20they've%20observed%20are%20substantial%3A%20AI%20is%20clearly%20making%20us%20better%2C%20faster%20workers.%20The%20numbers%20have%20prompted%20AI%20optimists%20to%20predict%20an%20economic%20boom%20and%20AI%20pessimists%20to%20worry%20about%20a%20future%20of%20fewer%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20behind%20those%20numbers%2C%20buried%20a%20little%20deeper%20in%20the%20studies%2C%20is%20the%20finding%20that%20interests%20me.%20The%20question%20isn't%20%3Cem%3Ehow%20much%3C%2Fem%3E%20AI%20helps%20out%20around%20the%20office%20but%20%3Cem%3Ewho%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20helps%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%2C%20the%20studies%20indicate%2C%20is%20making%20us%20more%20productive%20in%20a%20weird%20way.%20It's%20not%20helping%20%3Cem%3Eeveryone%3C%2Fem%3E%20get%20better%20at%20their%20jobs.%20It's%20mostly%20turbocharging%20workers%20who%20are%20bad%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20while%20doing%20little%20to%20aid%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20hindering%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20are%20already%20productive%20to%20begin%20with.%20AI%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20is%20raising%20overall%20productivity%20by%20narrowing%20the%20gap%20between%20high%20performers%20and%20low%20performers.%20It's%20equalizing%20white-collar%20work%20%E2%80%94%20a%20vast%20swath%20of%20the%20economy%20that%20has%20always%20been%20predicated%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20some%20people%20will%20inherently%20be%20much%2C%20much%20better%20at%20their%20jobs%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20get%20into%20the%20broader%20implications%20of%20the%20studies%2C%20let's%20start%20by%20reviewing%20their%20findings.%20Economists%20looked%20at%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20in%20six%20different%20areas%20of%20work%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreative%20writing.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Researchers%20tasked%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4535536%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrite%20a%20short%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20and%20without%20the%20help%20of%20an%20AI%20tool%20for%20generating%20ideas.%20Those%20who%20had%20no%20spark%20of%20their%20own%20became%20as%20much%20as%2011%25%20more%20novel%20and%2023%25%20more%20enjoyable%20with%20the%20help%20of%20AI.%20But%20the%20tool%20didn't%20benefit%20those%20who%20were%20already%20creative%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOffice%20memos.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Researchers%20had%20subjects%20complete%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4375283%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewriting%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20common%20in%20professional%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20think%20press%20releases%2C%20short%20reports%2C%20delicate%20emails.%20Access%20to%20AI%20made%20everyone%20faster%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20skill%20level%2C%20by%20an%20average%20of%2037%25.%20But%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20writing%2C%20AI%20mostly%20helped%20the%20low%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECoding.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Software%20engineers%20with%20fewer%20years%20of%20professional%20coding%20experience%20benefited%20much%20more%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2302.06590.pdf%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAI%2520assistance%2520can%2520increase%2520code%2Creal%252Dworld%2520impact%2520of%2520AI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccess%20to%20GitHub%20Copilot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20AI%20coding%20assistant%2C%20than%20veteran%20coders%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManagement%20consulting.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EResearchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4573321%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraded%20professional%20consultants%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E18%20knowledge-intensive%20tasks%20similar%20to%20what%20they%20actually%20do%20in%20their%20jobs.%20Access%20to%20GPT-4%20boosted%20the%20scores%20of%20low%20performers%20by%2043%25%2C%20compared%20with%20only%2017%25%20for%20high%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELaw%20school.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EResearchers%20administered%20an%20exam%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4539836%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20law%20students%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20and%20without%20GPT-4.%20Students%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20class%20got%20a%20big%20performance%20boost.%20But%20access%20to%20the%20tool%20actually%20hurt%20the%20grades%20of%20the%20students%20at%20the%20top%20of%20their%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECall-center%20work.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EResearchers%20measured%20the%20effects%20of%20a%20tailored%20AI%20tool%20that%20was%20introduced%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw31161%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20call%20center%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Novice%20and%20low-skilled%20workers%20became%2034%25%20more%20productive%2C%20while%20those%20with%20more%20experience%20and%20skill%20saw%20few%20benefits.%20Access%20to%20AI%20even%20slightly%20hindered%20the%20top%20performers%20on%20some%20measures%2C%20like%20conversation%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20yes%2C%20AI%20boosts%20productivity%20in%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20common%20office%20tasks%2C%20from%20repetitive%20work%20in%20low-paying%20call%20centers%20to%20complicated%20duties%20at%20elite%20management%20firms.%20And%20though%20most%20of%20the%20studies%20were%20hypothetical%20experiments%20in%20a%20lab%20%E2%80%94%20making%20their%20findings%20difficult%20to%20extrapolate%20to%20the%20real%20world%20%E2%80%94%20the%20call-center%20study%20looked%20at%20actual%20job%20performance%20at%20an%20actual%20company.%20But%20it's%20how%20AI%20increases%20productivity%20that%20should%20interest%20us%20the%20most.%20Together%2C%20the%20studies%20present%20a%20strong%20case%20that%20by%20disproportionately%20boosting%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%20this%20new%20generation%20of%20AI%20tools%20is%20narrowing%20the%20variation%20in%20job%20performance.%20In%20just%20a%20few%20short%20months%2C%20it's%20already%20doing%20what%20decades%20of%20education%20have%20failed%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20equalizing%20the%20American%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20stop%20to%20think%20about%20how%20large%20language%20models%20work%2C%20this%20finding%20makes%20sense.%20LLMs%20basically%20regurgitate%20what%20worked%20before%20%E2%80%94%20something%20the%20low%20performers%20can%20learn%20a%20lot%20from%2C%20but%20stuff%20the%20high%20performers%20already%20know.%20If%20you%20give%20everybody%20a%20cane%2C%20it'll%20speed%20up%20the%20slowest%20walkers%20the%20most.%20But%20it%20won't%20do%20much%20for%20Usain%20Bolt%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20might%20even%20slow%20him%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223185%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20working%20in%20an%20office%2C%20including%20one%20person%20in%20front%20of%20an%20early%20PC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65678642fe5bc6545ebd6f9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222817%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUnlike%20past%20technologies%20like%20the%20PC%2C%20which%20favored%20highly%20paid%20employees%20with%20college%20degrees%2C%20AI%20seems%20to%20be%20disproportionately%20helping%20those%20with%20fewer%20skills%20and%20less%20experience.%20%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20runs%20counter%20to%20how%20we're%20used%20to%20thinking%20about%20technology%20in%20the%20workplace.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20new%20technologies%20like%20industrial%20robots%2C%20the%20personal%20computer%2C%20and%20the%20internet%20have%20disproportionately%20aided%20highly%20skilled%20workers%20with%20college%20degrees%2C%20but%20they've%20done%20little%20to%20help%20(or%2C%20depending%20on%20who%20you%20ask%2C%20screwed%20over)%20those%20with%20fewer%20skills%20and%20less%20education.%20Economists%20call%20this%20skill-biased%20technological%20change%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20big%20reason%20income%20inequality%20has%20grown%20so%20much%20since%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20broader%20implications%20of%20the%20studies.%20If%20AI%20boosts%20the%20productivity%20of%20low%20performers%2C%20putting%20them%20on%20equal%20footing%20with%20the%20superstars%2C%20how%20is%20that%20going%20to%20change%20professional%20work%20as%20we%20know%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possibility%20is%20that%20AI%20could%20help%20reverse%20America's%20growing%20chasm%20of%20income%20inequality.%20Some%20of%20the%20inequality%20we%20see%20today%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20huge%20gaps%20in%20salary%20within%20many%20elite%20professions%20%E2%80%94%20of%20a%20superstar%20software%20engineer%2C%20say%2C%20who%20can%20churn%20out%20thousands%20of%20lines%20of%20code%20in%20the%20blink%20of%20an%20eye%2C%20compared%20to%20an%20average-performing%20techie.%20Presumably%2C%20the%20superstar%20gets%20paid%20more%20because%20they're%20so%20much%20better%20at%20their%20job%20than%20everyone%20else.%20But%20if%20AI%20makes%20it%20so%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-technology-end-of-coding-software-developers-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevery%20coder%20can%20blaze%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it'll%20be%20a%20lot%20harder%20for%20the%20hotshots%20to%20justify%20their%20astronomical%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20something%20the%20law-school%20study%20touches%20on.%20%26quot%3BThe%20legal%20profession%20has%20a%20well-known%20bimodal%20separation%20between%20'elite'%20and%20'nonelite'%20lawyers%20in%20pay%20and%20career%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20write.%20%26quot%3BBy%20helping%20to%20bring%20up%20the%20bottom%20(and%20even%20potentially%20bring%20down%20the%20top)%2C%20AI%20tools%20could%20be%20a%20significant%20force%20for%20equality%20in%20the%20practice%20of%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20true%20promise%20of%20AI%20lies%20in%20narrowing%20inequalities%20not%20%3Cem%3Ewithin%3C%2Fem%3E%20occupations%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3Ebetween%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethem.%20Software%20developers%20in%20the%20United%20States%20make%2C%20on%20average%2C%205.5%20times%20more%20than%20fast-food%20workers.%20If%20AI%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20a%20fast-food%20worker%20to%20move%20into%20a%20coding%20job%2C%20that's%20when%20we'll%20really%20start%20to%20see%20the%20income%20gap%20shrink.%20The%20GitHub%20Copilot%20study%20hinted%20at%20that%3A%20It%20found%20that%20the%20tool%20benefited%20novice%20programmers%20much%20more%20than%20expert%20ones.%20That%20could%20lower%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20for%20a%20whole%20new%20generation%20of%20aspiring%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20already%20one%20of%20the%20highly%20paid%20coders%2C%20this%20probably%20won't%20come%20as%20good%20news.%20Part%20of%20the%20reason%20programmers%20are%20paid%20so%20much%20is%20because%20there%20are%20so%20few%20of%20them.%20By%20allowing%20tons%20of%20people%20to%20flood%20into%20the%20occupation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20by%20turning%20crappy%20coders%20into%20decent%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20will%20almost%20certainly%20depress%20the%20sky-high%20salaries%20of%20those%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20profession.%20Education%20and%20expertise%20won't%20count%20for%20as%20much%20as%20they%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAdmittedly%2C%20this%20scenario%20I've%20laid%20out%20is%20an%20optimistic%20view%20of%20how%20AI%20will%20affect%20salaries.%20If%20it%20helps%20raise%20the%20skill%20level%20of%20subpar%20coders%2C%20then%20it%20will%20also%20raise%20their%20pay%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20necessarily.%20There's%20another%20way%20AI%20could%20reduce%20wage%20inequality%3A%20It%20could%20depress%20the%20pay%20of%20top%20earners%20without%20doing%20much%20to%20raise%20wages%20for%20those%20at%20the%20bottom.%20As%20productivity%20goes%20up%2C%20owners%20might%20opt%20to%20pocket%20the%20gains%20for%20themselves%2C%20lowering%20the%20salary%20ceiling%20rather%20than%20raising%20the%20salary%20floor.%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20we'll%20have%20less%20income%20inequality%20thanks%20to%20AI.%20But%20we'll%20all%20make%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20how%20AI%20is%20affecting%20the%20job%20market%20so%20far.%20In%20one%20study%2C%20researchers%20looked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4527336%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20happened%20to%20freelancers%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20online%20platform%20Upwork%20after%20the%20introduction%20of%20AI%20tools%20like%20ChatGPT.%20The%20number%20of%20jobs%20on%20the%20platform%20declined%2C%20and%20so%20did%20incomes.%20Those%20who%20were%20earning%20the%20most%20suffered%20the%20biggest%20hit.%20The%20top%20freelancers%20among%20those%20who%20offered%20image-based%20services%20received%207%25%20fewer%20jobs%20and%20watched%20their%20earnings%20tank%20by%20a%20staggering%2014%25.%20In%20economic%20terms%2C%20AI%20isn't%20upskilling%20the%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20deskilling%20it.%20By%20commodifying%20the%20talents%20of%20the%20best%20illustrators%2C%20it%20lowered%20their%20pay%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20same%20way%20mechanized%20looms%20destroyed%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20artisan%20weavers%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%20And%20AI%20systems%20are%20doing%20it%2C%20ironically%2C%20by%20feeding%20off%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20top%20performers%2C%20whose%20work%20provides%20the%20datasets%20they're%20trained%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20implications%20of%20these%20findings%20could%20go%20far%20beyond%20the%20question%20of%20pay%20and%20opportunity.%20We've%20organized%20much%20of%20white-collar%20work%20around%20the%20idea%20that%20there's%20a%20huge%20variation%20in%20both%20the%20quality%20and%20the%20quantity%20of%20work%20people%20produce.%20The%20entire%20idea%20of%20professionalism%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20is%20predicated%20on%20the%20notion%20of%20talent.%20Some%20people%20are%20just%20really%20good%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20the%20thinking%20goes%2C%20and%20it's%20worth%20throwing%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20at%20them%20to%20get%20them%20to%20work%20for%20you.%20That's%20why%20we%20receive%20raises%20for%20accumulating%20degrees%20and%20experience%20and%20expertise.%20And%20it's%20why%20companies%20have%20developed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-performance-evaluations-management-reviews-promotions-raises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplicated%20performance-management%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20weed%20out%20the%20lower%20performers%20and%20to%20reward%2C%20retain%2C%20and%20promote%20the%20superstars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20AI%20leads%20to%20a%20world%20in%20which%20employers%20get%20more%20or%20less%20the%20same%20work%20from%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20schooling%2C%20years%20on%20the%20job%2C%20or%20inherent%20talent%20%E2%80%94%20that%20opens%20up%20all%20kinds%20of%20wacky%20possibilities%20for%20the%20future%20of%20work.%20Will%20companies%20start%20paying%20everyone%20in%20a%20particular%20job%20the%20same%20salary%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20seniority%20level%3F%20Will%20promotions%20be%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%3F%20How%20will%20we%20raise%20our%20families%20and%20save%20for%20retirement%20if%20there's%20no%20opportunity%20for%20salary%20progression%3F%20Will%20HR%20departments%20dispense%20with%20time-consuming%20performance%20evaluations%20altogether%3F%20And%20if%20managers%20currently%20spend%20most%20of%20their%20time%20coaching%2C%20cajoling%2C%20and%20managing%20out%20their%20bottom%20performers%2C%20what%20happens%20to%20their%20jobs%20when%20there%20are%20no%20more%20bottom%20performers%20left%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20take%20the%20recent%20studies%20of%20AI%20at%20face%20value%2C%20the%20smart%20move%20for%20employers%20would%20be%20to%20hire%20the%20novices%20at%20cheap%20salaries%20and%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20veteran%20superstars%20who%20are%20earning%20the%20big%20bucks%20%E2%80%94%20implementing%20a%20%26quot%3BMoneyball%26quot%3B-style%20arbitrage%20for%20the%20ChatGPT%20age.%20But%20the%20thing%20is%2C%20I've%20spoken%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20executives%20over%20the%20past%20year%20about%20how%20they're%20rethinking%20their%20staffing%20plans%2C%20and%20not%20a%20single%20one%20has%20talked%20about%20scrapping%20their%20hotshot%20earners.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20of%20them%20have%20told%20me%2C%20in%20private%2C%20that%20they%20intend%20to%20do%20the%20exact%20opposite.%20They're%20aiming%20to%20hire%20fewer%20entry-level%20people%20straight%20out%20of%20school%2C%20since%20AI%20can%20increasingly%20take%20on%20the%20straightforward%2C%20well-defined%20tasks%20these%20younger%20workers%20have%20traditionally%20performed.%20They%20plan%20to%20bulk%20up%20on%20experts%20who%20can%20ace%20the%20complicated%20stuff%20that's%20still%20too%20hard%20for%20machines%20to%20perform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20to%20guess%2C%20though%2C%20I'd%20say%20that%20trend%20won't%20last.%20A%20few%20enterprising%20employers%20will%20go%20all%20in%20on%20hiring%20job%20candidates%20with%20less%20experience%20and%20boosting%20their%20performance%20with%20AI.%20They'll%20save%20boatloads%20of%20money%20on%20salaries%2C%20and%20from%20there%20the%20practice%20will%20inevitably%20spread.%20That%20will%20open%20up%20all%20kinds%20of%20opportunities%20for%20professional%20wannabes%20to%20get%20their%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20But%20for%20white-collar%20veterans%2C%20I%20suspect%20an%20onslaught%20is%20coming%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0one%20in%20which%20being%20good%20at%20your