ail%20was%20sent%20at%201%3A01%20a.m.%20ET%2C%20according%20to%20a%20time%20stamp%20on%20the%20email%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20That%20is%207%3A01%20a.m.%20local%20time%20in%20Stockholm%2C%20Sweden%2C%20where%20Spotify%20is%20headquartered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEconomic%20growth%20has%20slowed%20dramatically%20and%20capital%20has%20become%20more%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Ek%20said%20in%20the%20email%20and%20blog%20post.%20%26quot%3BSpotify%20is%20not%20an%20exception%20to%20these%20realities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20memo%20said%20workers%20would%20receive%20a%20calendar%20invite%20from%20HR%20within%20two%20hours%20for%20one-on-one%20conversations%20and%20that%20meetings%20would%20occur%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20working%20day%20on%20Tuesday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20blunt%2C%20many%20smart%2C%20talented%20and%20hard-working%20people%20will%20be%20departing%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Ek%20said%20in%20the%20memo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify's%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer%2C%20Katarina%20Berg%2C%20shared%20an%20FAQ%20document%20on%20the%20company's%20internal%20platform%20Workplace%20minutes%20after%20Ek's%20email%2C%20two%20employees%20til%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20the%20document%2C%20shared%20with%20BI%2C%20showed%20it%20said%20that%20people%20laid%20off%20were%20selected%20based%20on%3A%20%26quot%3Ba%20combination%20of%20factors%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%20organizational%20design%2C%20such%20as%20duplication%20of%20roles%2C%20streamlining%20layers%20to%20ensure%20efficiency%2C%20and%20optimizing%20our%20organization%20for%20the%20next%20chapter%20of%20Spotify.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20did%20not%20specify%20what%20departments%20and%20teams%20were%20impacted%20by%20the%20layoffs%2C%20or%20across%20which%20geographical%20locations%20the%20cuts%20would%20happen.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spotify.com%2Fuk%2Fabout-us%2Fcontact%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpotify%20has%20offices%20across%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20said%20in%20its%20FAQ%20document%20that%20%26quot%3Bultimately%2C%20it%20was%20a%20Leadership%20decision%26quot%3B%20as%20to%20who%20would%20lose%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20after%20Spotify%20axed%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-layoff-employees-jobs-reduce-costs-daniel-ek-2023-1%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E600%20employees%20in%20January%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20then%20a%20further%20200%20in%20June.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20Spotify%20employees%2C%20who%20did%20not%20wish%20to%20be%20identified%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20employees%20expected%20the%20further%20layoffs%20were%20looming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20shared%20a%20blog%20post%20in%20September%20titled%20%26quot%3BUnlocking%20Internal%20Mobility%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20said%20that%20internal%20mobility%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Btaking%20a%20higher%20priority.%26quot%3B%20The%20workers%20said%20it%20signalled%20the%20cuts%20were%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20also%20an%20internal%20memo%20about%20improving%20device%20security%20and%20specifically%20strict%20procedures%20around%20locking%20down%20laptops%20once%20employees%20leave%20the%20company%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20told%20BI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20memo%20titled%20%26quot%3BIntroducing%20new%20locking%20devices%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20sent%20by%20its%20IT%20department%20on%20Workplace%2C%20also%20indicated%20the%20layoffs%20were%20coming%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpotify%20declined%20to%20comment%20further%20when%20contacted%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20email%20that%20Ek%20sent%20to%20employees%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3ETeam%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20we've%20put%20significant%20emphasis%20on%20building%20Spotify%20into%20a%20truly%20great%20and%20sustainable%20business%20%E2%80%93%20one%20designed%20to%20achieve%20our%20goal%20of%20being%20the%20world's%20leading%20audio%20company%20and%20one%20that%20will%20consistently%20drive%20profitability%20and%20growth%20into%20the%20future.%20While%20we've%20made%20worthy%20strides%2C%20as%20I've%20shared%20many%20times%2C%20we%20still%20have%20work%20to%20do.%20Economic%20growth%20has%20slowed%20dramatically%20and%20capital%20has%20become%20more%20expensive.%20Spotify%20is%20not%20an%20exception%20to%20these%20realities.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThis%20brings%20me%20to%20a%20decision%20that%20will%20mean%20a%20significant%20step%20change%20for%20our%20company.%20To%20align%20Spotify%20with%20our%20future%20goals%20and%20ensure%20we%20are%20right-sized%20for%20the%20challenges%20ahead%2C%20I%20have%20made%20the%20difficult%20decision%20to%20reduce%20our%20total%20headcount%20by%20approximately%2017%25%20across%20the%20company.%20I%20recognize%20this%20will%20impact%20a%20number%20of%20individuals%20who%20have%20made%20valuable%20contributions.%20To%20be%20blunt%2C%20many%20smart%2C%20talented%20and%20hard-working%20people%20will%20be%20departing%20us.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFor%20those%20leaving%2C%20we're%20a%20better%20company%20because%20of%20your%20dedication%20and%20hard%20work.%20Thank%20you%20for%20sharing%20your%20talents%20with%20us.%20I%20hope%20you%20know%20that%20your%20contributions%20have%20impacted%20more%20than%20half%20a%20billion%20people%20and%20millions%20of%20artists%2C%20creators%2C%20and%20authors%20around%20the%20world%20in%20profound%20ways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI%20realize%20that%20for%20many%2C%20a%20reduction%20of%20this%20size%20will%20feel%20surprisingly%20large%20given%20the%20recent%20positive%20earnings%20report%20and%20our%20performance.%20We%20debated%20making%20smaller%20reductions%20throughout%202024%20and%202025.%20Yet%2C%20considering%20the%20gap%20between%20our%20financial%20goal%20state%20and%20our%20current%20operational%20costs%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20a%20substantial%20action%20to%20rightsize%20our%20costs%20was%20the%20best%20option%20to%20accomplish%20our%20objectives.%20While%20I%20am%20convinced%20this%20is%20the%20right%20action%20for%20our%20company%2C%20I%20also%20understand%20it%20will%20be%20incredibly%20painful%20for%20our%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETo%20understand%20this%20decision%2C%20I%20think%20it%20is%20important%20to%20assess%20Spotify%20with%20a%20clear%2C%20objective%20lens.%20In%202020%20and%202021%2C%20we%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20opportunity%20presented%20by%20lower-cost%20capital%20and%20invested%20significantly%20in%20team%20expansion%2C%20content%20enhancement%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20new%20verticals.%20These%20investments%20generally%20worked%2C%20contributing%20to%20Spotify's%20increased%20output%20and%20the%20platform's%20robust%20growth%20this%20past%20year.%20However%2C%20we%20now%20find%20ourselves%20in%20a%20very%20different%20environment.%20And%20despite%20our%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20costs%20this%20past%20year%2C%20our%20cost%20structure%20for%20where%20we%20need%20to%20be%20is%20still%20too%20big.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWhen%20we%20look%20back%20on%202022%20and%202023%2C%20it%20has%20truly%20been%20impressive%20what%20we%20have%20accomplished.%20But%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20much%20of%20this%20output%20was%20linked%20to%20having%20more%20resources.%20By%20most%20metrics%2C%20we%20were%20more%20productive%20but%20less%20efficient.%20We%20need%20to%20be%20both.%20While%20we%20have%20done%20some%20work%20to%20mitigate%20this%20challenge%20and%20become%20more%20efficient%20in%202023%2C%20we%20still%20have%20a%20ways%20to%20go%20before%20we%20are%20both%20productive%20and%20efficient.%20Today%2C%20we%20still%20have%20too%20many%20people%20dedicated%20to%20supporting%20work%20and%20even%20doing%20work%20around%20the%20work%20rather%20than%20contributing%20to%20opportunities%20with%20real%20impact.%20More%20people%20need%20to%20be%20focused%20on%20delivering%20for%20our%20key%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%93%20creators%20and%20consumers.%20In%20two%20words%2C%20we%20have%20to%20become%20relentlessly%20resourceful.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI%20know%20you%20will%20all%20be%20anxious%20to%20hear%20the%20next%20steps%20about%20how%20this%20process%20will%20work.%20If%20you%20are%20an%20impacted%20employee%2C%20you%20will%20receive%20a%20calendar%20invite%20within%20the%20next%20two%20hours%20from%20HR%20for%20a%20one-on-one%20conversation.%20These%20meetings%20will%20take%20place%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20and%20while%20%3Cstrong%3EKatarina%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20will%20provide%20more%20detail%20on%20all%20of%20the%20specifics%2C%20please%20know%20the%20following%20will%20apply%20to%20all%20of%20these%20bandmates%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ESeverance%20pay%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3EWe%20will%20start%20with%20a%20baseline%20for%20all%20employees%2C%20with%20the%20average%20employee%20receiving%20approximately%20five%20months%20of%20severance.%20This%20will%20be%20calculated%20based%20on%20local%20notice%20period%20requirements%20and%20employee%20tenure.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EPTO%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20All%20accrued%20and%20unused%20vacation%20will%20be%20paid%20out%20to%20any%20departing%20employee.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EHealthcare%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20We%20will%20continue%20to%20cover%20healthcare%20for%20employees%20during%20their%20severance%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EImmigration%20support%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20For%20employees%20whose%20immigration%20status%20is%20connected%20with%20their%20employment%2C%20HRBPs%20are%20working%20with%20each%20impacted%20individual%20in%20concert%20with%20our%20mobility%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ECareer%20Support%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EAll%20employees%20will%20be%20eligible%20for%20outplacement%20services%20for%20two%20months.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Csection%3EFor%20the%20team%20that%20will%20remain%20at%20Spotify%2C%20I%20know%20this%20decision%20will%20be%20difficult%20for%20many.%20Please%20know%20we%20are%20focused%20on%20treating%20our%20impacted%20colleagues%20with%20the%20respect%20and%20compassion%20they%20deserve.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20Ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20decision%20to%20reduce%20our%20team%20size%20is%20a%20hard%20but%20crucial%20step%20towards%20forging%20a%20stronger%2C%20more%20efficient%20Spotify%20for%20the%20future.%20But%20it%20also%20highlights%20that%20we%20need%20to%20change%20how%20we%20work.%20In%20Spotify's%20early%20days%2C%20our%20success%20was%20hard%20won.%20We%20had%20limited%20resources%20and%20had%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20every%20asset.%20Our%20ingenuity%20and%20creativity%20were%20what%20set%20us%20apart.%20As%20we've%20grown%2C%20we've%20moved%20too%20far%20away%20from%20this%20core%20principle%20of%20resourcefulness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20Spotify%20of%20tomorrow%20must%20be%20defined%20by%20being%20relentlessly%20resourceful%20in%20the%20ways%20we%20operate%2C%20innovate%2C%20and%20tackle%20problems.%20This%20kind%20of%20resourcefulness%20transcends%20the%20basic%20definition%20%E2%80%93%20it's%20about%20preparing%20for%20our%20next%20phase%2C%20where%20being%20lean%20is%20not%20just%20an%20option%20but%20a%20necessity.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EEmbracing%20this%20leaner%20structure%20will%20also%20allow%20us%20to%20invest%20our%20profits%20more%20strategically%20back%20into%20the%20business.%20With%20a%20more%20targeted%20approach%2C%20every%20investment%20and%20initiative%20becomes%20more%20impactful%2C%20offering%20greater%20opportunities%20for%20success.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20step%20back%3B%20it's%20a%20strategic%20reorientation.%20We're%20still%20committed%20to%20investing%20and%20making%20bold%20bets%2C%20but%20now%2C%20with%20a%20more%20focused%20approach%2C%20ensuring%20Spotify's%20continued%20profitability%20and%20ability%20to%20innovate.%20Lean%20doesn't%20mean%20small%20ambitions%3B%20it%20means%20smarter%2C%20more%20impactful%20paths%20to%20achieve%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EToday%20is%20a%20difficult%20but%20important%20day%20for%20the%20company.%20To%20be%20very%20clear%2C%20my%20commitment%20to%20our%20mission%20and%20belief%20in%20our%20ability%20to%20achieve%20it%20has%20never%20been%20stronger.%20I%20hope%20you%20will%20join%20me%20on%20Wednesday%20for%20Unplugged%20to%20discuss%20how%20we%20move%20forward%20together.%20A%20reduction%20of%20this%20size%20will%20make%20it%20necessary%20to%20change%20the%20way%20we%20work%2C%20and%20we%20will%20share%20much%20more%20about%20what%20this%20will%20mean%20in%20the%20days%20and%20weeks%20ahead.%20Just%20as%202023%20marked%20a%20new%20chapter%20for%20us%2C%20so%20will%202024%20as%20we%20build%20an%20even%20stronger%20Spotify.%C2%A0%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%E2%80%93%20Daniel%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20current%20or%20former%20Spotify%20employee%3F%20Got%20a%20tip%3F%3Cbr%3EContact%20Jyoti%20Mann%20at%20%3Cu%3Ejmann%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%20or%20via%20direct%20message%20on%20X%20%40jyoti_mann1.%20Reach%20out%20using%20a%20non-work%20device.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-layoffs-read-memo-ceo-sent-employees-announcing-cuts-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701682636000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65578c0d22cf74a5739944bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-layoffs-read-memo-ceo-sent-employees-announcing-cuts-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Spotify%20CEO%20Daniel%20Ek%20told%20employees%20in%20an%20email%20announcing%20the%20layoffs%20that%20%26quot%3Bmany%20smart%2C%20talented%20and%20hard-working%20people%20will%20be%20departing%20us.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmann%40insider.com%20(Jyoti%20Mann)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A73%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-layoffs-read-memo-ceo-sent-employees-announcing-cuts-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Decomposing%20Bodies%20of%20Four%20Babies%E2%80%99%3A%20A%20Grim%20Reminder%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20War%20That%20Has%20Not%20Spared%20Children%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELast%20month%2C%20a%20Gazan%20journalist%20ventured%20into%20the%20hospital%20to%20find%20an%20awful%20visual%3A%20decomposing%20bodies%20of%20four%20babies%2C%20eaten%20by%20worms%2C%20blackened%20by%20mold%2C%20mauled%20by%20stray%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl-Nasr%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Hospital%20director%20Bakr%20Qaoud%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20at%20the%20height%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20assault%20on%20northern%20Gaza%20in%20November%2C%20everybody%20was%20ordered%20to%20evacuate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20whereabouts%20of%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20infants%2C%20born%20premature%2C%20were%20not%20known%20after%20a%20month%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20total%20of%20five%20infants%20Qaoud%20was%20taking%20care%20of.%20All%20of%20them%20were%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20needed%20oxygen%2C%20and%20medication%20administered%20at%20regular%20intervals.%20There%20were%20no%20portable%20respirators%20or%20incubators%20to%20transport%20them.%20Without%20life%20support%2C%20the%20nurse%20feared%2C%20they%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20survive%20an%20evacuation%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20the%20Israeli%20Defense%20Force%20delivered%20an%20ultimatum%20on%20November%2010%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F12%2F03%2Fgaza-premature-babies-dead-nasr%2F%5C%22%3Ehad%20no%20choice%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20to%20carry%20the%20baby%20he%20thought%20will%20survive%20with%20a%20temporary%20cut%20to%20his%20oxygen%20supply.%20He%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20other%20four%20babies%2C%20reluctantly%2C%20with%20their%20breathing%20machines%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20forces%20told%20al-Nasr%E2%80%99s%20staff%20they%20had%20to%20leave%2C%20according%20to%20Qaoud.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20sent%20us%20a%20map%20for%20a%20safe%20route%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20WhatsApp%20message.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20gave%20us%20half%20an%20hour%20to%20go%20out.%20Otherwise%2C%20they%20will%20bombard%20the%20hospital.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20staff%20was%20promised%20that%20ambulances%20will%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20take%20the%20patients%20from%20al-Nasr%20and%20al-Rantisi%2C%20a%20pediatric%20cancer%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20telephone%20conversation%20with%20the%20Coordinator%20of%20Government%20Activities%20in%20the%20Territories%2C%20an%20arm%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20defense%20ministry%2C%20the%20al-Rantisi%20official%20requested%20ambulances.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2Fidfofficial%2F5131%5C%22%3Erecording%20of%20that%20call%20released%20by%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20%3C%2Fa%3EForces%2C%20a%20senior%20COGAT%20officer%20responds%20in%20Arabic%3A%20%E2%80%9CNo%20problem.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20senior%20COGAT%20officer%20tells%20the%20al-Rantisi%20official%20that%20he%20will%20%E2%80%9Carrange%20coordination%E2%80%9D%20for%20ambulances.%20He%20gives%20the%20precise%20route%20that%20medical%20staff%20should%20take%20out%20of%20the%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20al-Rantisi%20official%20reminds%20COGAT%20that%20staff%20will%20also%20be%20evacuating%20al-Nasr.%20The%20COGAT%20officer%20acknowledges%20the%20reminder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EQaoud%2C%20too%2C%20said%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccoordination%20with%20the%20Red%20Cross%20and%20Israeli%20army%20that%20we%20will%20go%20out%20and%20then%20these%20cases%20will%20be%20later%20evacuated%20to%20another%20hospital%20that%20was%20safe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F01%2Fbirth-and-death-intertwined-gaza-strip%5C%22%3EHuman%20Rights%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Gaza%20authorities%20said%20that%20more%20than%206%2C000%20Palestinian%20children%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20since%20the%20Hamas-led%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%20There%20are%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fprogram%2Finside-story%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Fwhy-have-so-many-palestinian-children-been-killed-by-israel%5C%22%3Ewho%20are%20still%20missing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20buried%20under%20the%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Israeli%20authorities%2C%20the%20October%207%20attack%20killed%20at%20least%2033%20children%2C%20and%2040%20children%20were%20taken%20hostage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%